keep%20everything%20in%20cash%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHolding%20onto%20your%20cash%20may%20seem%20like%20the%20safer%20option%20compared%20to%20risking%20it%20on%20the%20market.%20But%20in%20actuality%2C%20your%20money%20is%20losing%20value%20due%20to%20inflation%20diminishing%20the%20purchasing%20power%20of%20the%20US%20dollar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20though%20cash%20yields%20are%20better%20than%20five%20or%20six%20years%20ago%2C%20they're%20still%20low%20compared%20to%20inflation%2C%26quot%3B%20Tom%20Graff%2C%20chief%20investment%20officer%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Ffacet-wealth-review%5C%22%3EFacet%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BBy%20holding%20onto%20cash%2C%20you're%20functionally%20not%20making%20any%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20way%20to%20combat%20inflation%20and%20preserve%20wealth%20is%20by%20investing%20in%20a%20diversified%20portfolio%20of%20stocks%2C%20bonds%2C%20and%20other%20securities.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-the-sp-500%5C%22%3ES%26amp%3BP%20500%3C%2Fa%3E%20index%2C%20a%20popular%20stock%20market%20benchmark%2C%20has%20a%20historic%20average%20annual%20return%20of%2010%25%20that%20far%20outperforms%20the%20US%20inflation%20rate%20of%202.6%25.%20Savings%20accounts%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20only%20have%20an%20average%20return%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Faverage-savings-account-interest-rate%5C%22%3E0.43%25%20APY%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20your%20bank%20account%20is%20still%20the%20right%20place%20for%20money%20you%20know%20you%20need%20to%20pay%20off%20short-term%20expenses%20like%20rent%2C%20groceries%2C%20and%20debt.%20Only%20invest%20money%20you%20won't%20need%20access%20to%20for%20at%20least%20several%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20all%20felt%20inflation%20over%20the%20last%20several%20years%20eat%20away%20at%20our%20earnings%20and%20our%20spending%20power%2C%26quot%3B%20Corbin%20Blackwell%2C%20senior%20financial%20planner%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbetterment-review%5C%22%3EBetterment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BYou%20aren't%20getting%20anything%20from%20your%20savings%20account%2C%20but%20investing%20keeps%20pace%20with%20inflation.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20You're%20experiencing%20extreme%20highs%20and%20lows%20in%20your%20portfolio%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20sign%20that%20you're%20not%20investing%20enough%20in%20the%20stock%20market%20is%20if%20you're%20experiencing%20extreme%20highs%20and%20lows%20every%20time%20you%20look%20at%20your%20portfolio's%20performance%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Blackwell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20thoroughly%20invested%20in%20the%20market%20doesn't%20necessarily%20mean%20buying%20more%20stocks%20or%20increasing%20the%20size%20of%20your%20portfolio%2C%20she%20says.%20Rather%2C%20it%20refers%20to%20diversifying%20your%20assets%20to%20gain%20exposure%20from%20multiple%20areas%20of%20the%20market.%C2%A0Someone%20who%20owns%20100%20shares%20of%20different%20technology%20companies%20is%20less%20diversified%20than%20someone%20who%20owns%20half%20that%20amount%20of%20shares%20but%20has%20exposure%20to%20a%20mix%20of%20market%20sectors%20like%20health%20care%2C%20real%20estate%2C%20financials%2C%20tech%2C%20and%20communication%20services.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilar%20to%20a%20roller%20coaster%2C%20an%20investment%20portfolio%20that%20lacks%20proper%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-diversification%5C%22%3Ediversification%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20vulnerable%20to%20frequent%20market%20swings.%20These%20extreme%20highs%2C%20although%20thrilling%2C%20prevent%20your%20portfolio%20from%20growing%20at%20a%20steady%20and%20reliable%20pace.%20Instead%2C%20you're%20at%20greater%20risk%20of%20a%20major%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDiversifying%20your%20investments%20across%20various%20market%20sectors%20is%20a%20proven%20strategy%20to%20mitigate%20risk%20and%20enhance%20your%20portfolio's%20performance.%20By%20spreading%20your%20investments%2C%20you%20can%20better%20weather%20market%20fluctuations%20and%20capitalize%20on%20opportunities%20in%20different%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20need%20to%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20to%20have%20a%20diversified%20portfolio%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Blackwell.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20buy%20a%20share%20of%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-an-etf%5C%22%3EETF%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20already%20diversified%20in%20and%20of%20itself.%20But%20you%20shouldn't%20just%20buy%20one%20ETF%2C%20either.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20know%20where%20to%20start%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-find-financial-advisor%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20hard.%20SmartAsset's%20free%20tool%20matches%20you%20with%20up%20to%20three%20fiduciary%20financial%20advisors%20that%20serve%20your%20area%20in%20minutes.%20Each%20advisor%20has%20been%20vetted%20by%20SmartAsset%20and%20is%20held%20to%20a%20fiduciary%20standard%20to%20act%20in%20your%20best%20interests.%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Start%20your%20search%20now.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20You%20never%20increase%20your%20retirement%20contributions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20beginning%20of%20your%20working%20career%2C%20you%20likely%20could%20only%20contribute%20a%20small%20percentage%20of%20your%20paycheck%20to%20your%20401(k)%20or%20another%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbest-retirement-plans%5C%22%3Ebest%20retirement%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20did%20you%20increase%20your%20contributions%20the%20last%20time%20you%20got%20a%20raise%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20you%20make%20more%20money%2C%20contribute%20more%20toward%20your%20retirement%20plan%20to%20make%20up%20for%20the%20years%20you%20could%20only%20contribute%20a%20little.%20This%20is%20especially%20important%20if%20your%20employer%20offers%20a%20match%2C%20as%20this%20is%20essentially%20free%20money.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20retirement%20may%20feel%20light%20years%20away%2C%20time%20is%20paramount%20as%20retirement%20savings%20steadily%20grow%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fwhat-is-compound-interest%5C%22%3Ecompound%20interest%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20long-term%20investment%20opportunities.%20As%20mentioned%20before%2C%20holding%20onto%20loads%20of%20cash%20diminishes%20its%20spending%20power.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlackwell%20noted%20that%20investing%20is%20a%20crucial%20step%20in%20securing%20retirement%20as%20you%20can't%20get%20back%20that%20time%20that%20you%20missed%2C%20and%20relying%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-social-security%5C%22%3ESocial%20Security%3C%2Fa%3E%20alone%20isn't%20recommended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20have%20any%20help%20in%20the%20form%20of%20investment%20gains%20and%20compound%20interest%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20have%20a%20really%20hard%20time%20affording%20that%20retirement%2C%20especially%20when%20life%20expectancy%20is%20so%20long%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Blackwell%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20You're%20focused%20on%20short-term%20volatility%20rather%20than%20long-term%20gains%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20sign%20of%20underinvesting%20is%20if%20you%20find%20yourself%20holding%20back%20from%20participating%20in%20the%20current%20market%20due%20to%20its%20short-term%20volatility.%20The%20market's%20daily%20fluctuations%20can%20look%20intimidating%2C%20especially%20if%20you're%20new%20to%20stock%20investing%2C%20but%20not%20all%20volatility%20is%20bad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlackwell%20explains%20that%20financial%20advisors%20prefer%20people%20to%20invest%20long-term%20as%20many%20opportunities%20need%20time%20in%20the%20market%20to%20accumulate%20gains.%20%26quot%3BInvesting%20isn't%20about%20the%20big%20wins%2C%26quot%3B%20She%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20not%20enough%20certainty%20in%20any%20portfolio%20to%20only%20benefit%20from%20the%20upside.%20It's%20always%20a%20risk%2C%20return%20trade-off.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGraff%20notes%20that%20current%20economic%20and%20political%20factors%20impact%20people's%20perspective%20and%20optimism%20about%20the%20market%20and%20the%20US%20economy%20as%20a%20whole.%20However%2C%20those%20circumstances%20generally%20impact%20the%20short-term%20rather%20than%20the%20actual%20long-term%20potential%20of%20the%20average%20investor's%20portfolio.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20always%20something%2C%20and%20when%20the%20market%20has%20been%20up%20a%20lot%2C%20anything%20that%20goes%20wrong%20could%20be%20a%20downturn%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Graff.%20%26quot%3BAt%20some%20point%20there's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-a-bear-market%5C%22%3Ebear%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20again%2C%20but%20timing%20that%20is%20so%20difficult.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20there's%20no%20better%20time%20to%20invest%20in%20the%20market%20than%20the%20present%2C%20as%20you%20risk%20missing%20out%20on%20growth%20opportunities%20by%20focusing%20on%20the%20short%20term%20instead%20of%20having%20a%20long-term%20perspective.%20Moreover%2C%20long-term%20investing%20is%20generally%20less%20risky%20and%20provides%20opportunities%20for%20recovery%20from%20market%20downturns.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20fair%20to%20tell%20investors%20not%20to%20worry%20about%20problems%20like%20inflation.%20Instead%2C%20the%20real%20advice%20is%20to%20use%20that%20time%20to%20your%20advantage%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Graff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-not-investing-enough-money-stock-market-soars-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733432274000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6751d4d68fbb2783ed2ffca5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-not-investing-enough-money-stock-market-soars-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Combat%20inflation%20and%20preserve%20the%20purchasing%20power%20of%20your%20money%20by%20investing%20in%20the%20stock%20market.%20Experts%20list%20signs%20you%20may%20be%20underinvesting.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Tessa%20Campbell)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-not-investing-enough-money-stock-market-soars-2024-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20complete%20timeline%20of%20Meghan%20Markle%20and%20Prince%20Harry's%20relationship%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224742%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Meghan%20Markle%20and%20Prince%20Harry%20in%20December%2C%202017.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62ea3d04c6987600183c5f9c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223556%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMeghan%20Markle%20and%20Prince%20Harry%20in%20December%202017.%3Cp%3EKarwai%20Tang%2FWireImage%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business