0which%20historically%20contributed%20the%20most%2C%20is%20ironically%20the%20best%20equipped%20with%20the%20technological%20and%20economic%20means%20to%20address%20this%20challenge%2C%26quot%3B%20Rangreji%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20criticised%20rich%20countries%20for%20enjoying%20the%20benefits%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20while%20discouraging%20developing%20nations%20from%20using%20their%20own%20energy%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCountries%20which%20have%20reaped%20development%20benefits%20from%20exploiting%20fossil%20fuels%20demand%20developing%20countries%20to%20not%20utilise%20the%20national%20energy%20resources%20available%20to%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20also%20slammed%20the%20lack%20of%20action%20on%20climate-finance%20commitments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20USD%20100%20billion%20pledged%20at%20the%20Copenhagen%20COP%20in%202009%20by%20developed%20country%20parties%20and%20the%20doubling%20of%20the%20contribution%20to%20the%20Adaptation%20Fund%20have%20not%20yet%20been%20translated%20into%20any%20concrete%20actions%2C%26quot%3B%20India%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20called%20the%20new%20climate%20finance%20package%20for%20the%20Global%20South%20agreed%20at%20COP29%20in%20Azerbaijan's%20Baku%20%26quot%3Btoo%20little%2C%20too%20distant%26quot%3B%20to%20meet%20the%20urgent%20needs%20of%20developing%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20stressed%20the%20principle%20of%20fairness%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20contribution%20to%20global%20environmental%20degradation%20is%20unequal%2C%20the%20responsibility%20should%20also%20be%20unequal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20also%20reaffirmed%20its%20commitment%20to%20its%20climate%20targets%20under%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%2C%20but%20warned%20against%20overburdening%20its%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20limit%20on%20how%20much%20we%20burden%20our%20citizens%2C%20even%20when%20India%20is%20pursuing%20Sustainable%20D