22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompressed%20stabilised%20earth%20bricks%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20were%20enthusiastic.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20they%20discovered%2C%20not%20only%20do%20the%20bricks%20add%20a%20bold%20dynamic%20to%20the%20structure%20but%20they%20also%20boast%2080%20percent%20less%20energy%20consumption%20while%20achieving%20thermal%20comfort.%20The%20architects%20share%20that%20the%20bricks%20they%20used%20were%20made%20using%20a%20natural%20mix%20of%20red%20soil%2C%20sand%20and%20%3Cem%3Emurum%3C%2Fem%3E%20(crumbled%20rock)%20stabilised%20with%20five%20percent%20cement.%20This%20ensured%20their%20durability.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fsustainable-architecture-4-1733298121.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20SUHRC%20Symbiosis%20University%20Hospital%20and%20Research%20Centre%2C%20Lavale%2C%20Pune%20has%20been%20built%20with%20compressed%20stabilised%20earth%20bricks%20(CSEBs)%20that%20are%20good%20candidates%20to%20replace%20fired%20bricks%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fsustainable-architecture-4-1733298121.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fsustainable-architecture-4-1733298121-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fsustainable-architecture-4-1733298121-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fsustainable-architecture-4-1733298121-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fsustainable-architecture-4-1733298121-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-386133%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20SUHRC%20Symbiosis%20University%20Hospital%20and%20Research%20Centre%2C%20Lavale%2C%20Pune%20has%20been%20built%20with%20compressed%20stabilised%20earth%20bricks%20(CSEBs)%20that%20are%20good%20candidates%20to%20replace%20fired%20bricks%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20IMK%20Architects%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20extend%20the%20project%E2%80%99s%20scope%20of%20sustainability%2C%20the%20architects%20ensured%20that%20the%20bricks%20were%20made%20on-site%20by%20using%20a%20block-making%20machine%2C%20thus%20cutting%20the%20emission%20of%20carbon%2C%20while%20also%20employing%20local%20labour%20to%20sun%20dry%20instead%20of%20kiln-fire%20the%20bricks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArchitects%2C%20take%20notes%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Not%20all%20soils%20may%20be%20suitable%20for%20CSEB.%20Avoid%20using%20topsoil%20and%20organic%20soils.%20The%20type%20of%20stabiliser%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20added%20to%20the%20mix%20will%20depend%20upon%20the%20soil%20in%20question.%20Cement%20works%20best%20for%20sandy%20soils%2C%20while%20lime%20works%20best%20for%20clayey%20soils.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E5.%20Acetylated%20wood%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWood%2C%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F305212%2Feco-friendly-sustainable-house-in-thrissur-kerala-using-bamboo-bricks-wood-red-oxide-saves-electricity%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econstruction%20material%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20draws%20concerns%20for%20its%20responsiveness%20to%20environmental%20variables.%20So%2C%20imagine%20a%20variety%20of%20wood%20that%20performs%20well%20irrespective%20of%20the%20surroundings%3B%20one%20that%20can%20tolerate%20extreme%20temperatures%20as%20well%20as%20endure%20water%20exposure!%20When%20architect%20Vijay%20Dahiya%2C%20partner%20at%20team3%2C%20discovered%20acetylated%20wood%2C%20he%20was%20excited%20to%20try%20it%20out%20in%20one%20of%20his%20projects%2C%20%E2%80%98Mehra%20Residence%E2%80%99%2C%20in%20Delhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fsustainable-architecture-5_11zon-1733298312.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Mehra%20Residence%20in%20Delhi%20has%20been%20constructed%20using%20acetylated%20wood%20which%20lends%20anti-fungal%20properties%20to%20the%20structure%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Vijay%20Dahiya%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fsustainable-architecture-5_11zon-1733298312.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fsustainable-architecture-5_11zon-1733298312-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fsustainable-architecture-5_11zon-1733298312-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fsustainable-architecture-5_11zon-1733298312-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fsustainable-architecture-5_11zon-1733298312-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-386136%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20Mehra%20Residence%20in%20Delhi%20has%20been%20constructed%20using%20acetylated%20wood%20which%20lends%20anti-fungal%20properties%20to%20the%20structure%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Vijay%20Dahiya%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbout%20the%20material%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Aside%20from%20the%20initial%20cost%2C%20Vijay%20says%20there%20are%20only%20advantages%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20combined%20with%20water-based%2C%20low-VOC%20(volatile%20organic%20compounds)%20finishes%2C%20it%20maintains%20the%20eco-friendly%20integrity.%E2%80%9D%20In%20addition%20to%20this%2C%20acetylation%20enhances%20the%20wood%E2%80%99s%20resistance%20against%20fungal%20decay%2C%20a%20study%20found.%20When%20the%20environmental%20impacts%20of%20acetylated%20Scots%20pine%2C%20tropical%20hardwood%20(Azobe)%2C%20and%20non-renewable%20materials%20(steel%2C%20concrete)%20were%20compared%2C%20the%20results%20showed%20that%20acetylated%20wood%20has%20a%20considerably%20lower%20carbon%20footprint%20than%20steel%2C%20concrete%20and%20unsustainably%20sourced%20Azobe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArchitects%2C%20take%20notes%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Considering%20the%20material%20is%20wood%2C%20Vijay%20cautions%20that%20it%20should%20be%20sourced%20from%20sustainable%20forests.%20%E2%80%9CTrees%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F299507%2Feco-friendly-mud-red-stone-kerala-home-skylights-elliptical-windows-save-on-electric-bills%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enatural%20carbon%20sequesters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20when%20used%20in%20construction%2C%20wood%20can%20further%20lock%20in%20that%20sequestered%20carbon%20for%20decades.%20If%20sourced%20from%20fast-growing%20species%20like%20spruce%20or%20pine%2C%20and%20sustainable%2C%20replenishable%20forests%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20win-win.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Arunava%20Banerjee%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESources%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fijcsm.springeropen.com%2Farticles%2F10.1186%2Fs40069-022-00569-x%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUtilization%20of%20Solid%20Waste%20in%20the%20Production%20of%20Autoclaved%20Aerated%20Concrete%20and%20Their%20Effects%20on%20its%20Physio-mechanical%20and%20Microstructural%20Properties%3A%20Alternative%20Sources%2C%20Characterization%2C%20and%20Performance%20Insights%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20by%20